<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFBAFFE0FF1CF9944ADDFDDE" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBAFFE0FF1CF994489AF8AB" blockId="11.[113,764,1601,1946]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FF1CF99449B5F9A8" box="[151,215,1602,1625]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Notes.</emphasis>
– In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FE4AF9944BFCF9A8" author="BURMAN" box="[449,670,1601,1626]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="235" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 235)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a plate in RUMPHIUS’s 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FE1AF9B44BE9F98B" box="[401,651,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Herbarium Amboinense</emphasis>
(1750: 70, tab. 30, fig. 1) and a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FED3F95448DFF96B" box="[344,445,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Kleynhoff</emphasis>
collection in his herbarium. Thus a lectotypification is necessary. The only original material in G-PREL is a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FEDBF91448ECF928" box="[336,398,1730,1753]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Pryon</emphasis>
collection from 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFBAFFE0FDB4F9144B08F928" box="[575,618,1730,1753]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Java</collectingRegion>
that Burman erroneously attributed to 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FEF4F9344884F90B" box="[383,486,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Kleynhoff:</emphasis>
the polynomial “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FD17F93448F8F8EB" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FD17F9344BADF90B" box="[668,719,1762,1786]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Filix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Filix</taxonomicName>
non ramosa foliis integris alternis
</emphasis>
” cited in the protologue appears in Pryon’s typical handwriting on the sheet. This collections is here designated as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBAFFE0FEB0F89448FEF8AB" box="[315,412,1858,1882]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="49D32A11FFBAFFE0FE21F8944889F8AB" box="[426,491,1858,1882]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[136,164,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[301,1309,276,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[301,1309,276,1863]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. – Lectotype of Polypodium simplex Burm. f. in G-PREL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5708793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5708793/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBAFFE0FF1CF8B44ADDFDDE" blockId="11.[113,764,1601,1946]" lastBlockId="11.[801,1452,279,559]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">
The 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FF44F8B44872F888" box="[207,272,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen in G-PREL clearly represents a species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FEC7F8544B22F86B" authority="(Bory) J. Sm. It" authorityName="J. Sm. It" baseAuthorityName="Bory" box="[332,576,1922,1946]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Drynaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FEC7F85448CCF868" box="[332,430,1922,1945]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Drynaria</emphasis>
(Bory) J. Sm.
</taxonomicName>
It corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FCAAFECE4D08FEDE" authority="(Sw.) Bedd." authorityName="Bedd." baseAuthorityName="Sw." box="[801,1130,279,303]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Drynaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidula">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FCAAFECE4ABDFEDE" box="[801,991,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Drynaria rigidula</emphasis>
(Sw.) Bedd.
</taxonomicName>
, showing a sterile frond with anastomosing veins and narrow pinnae articulate to rachis. 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FCAAFE814AA4FE9E" author="BURMAN" box="[801,966,343,367]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768)</bibRefCitation>
’s 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FC53FE814DFCFE9E" box="[984,1182,343,367]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FC53FE814DFCFE9E" box="[984,1182,343,367]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Polypodium simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
predates 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FA8AFE814CFDFE9E" author="SWARTZ" box="[1281,1439,343,367]" firstAuthor="SWARTZ" journalOrPublisher="J. Bot. (Schrader)" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" pagination="3 - 120" part="1800" refId="ref10356" refString="SWARTZ, O. (1801). Genera et species filicum. J. Bot. (Schrader) 1800 (2): 3 - 120." title="Genera et species filicum" type="journal article" year="1801">SWARTZ (1801)</bibRefCitation>
’s 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FCAAFEAE4AFFFE7E" box="[801,925,375,399]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidulum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FCAAFEAE4AFFFE7E" box="[801,925,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">P. rigidulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In order to allow the further use of a well-known and widely used fern name (
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FBD0FE414D13FE5E" box="[1115,1137,407,431]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
. Smith, pers. comm.) and to avoid disadvantageous nomenclatural changes entailed by the strict application of the 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FB97FE014D2DFE1E" box="[1052,1103,471,495]" country="Colombia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xsgz-nxkh" name="Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Museo de Historia Natural" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">ICN</collectionCode>
rules (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FB1CFE014C15FE1E" author="TURLAND" box="[1175,1399,471,495]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="TURLAND" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref10318" refString="TURLAND, N. J., J. H. WIERSEMA, F. R. BARRIE, W. GREUTER, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, P. S. HERENDEEN, S. KNAPP, W. - H. KUSBER, D. - Z. LI, K. MARHOLD, T. W. MAY, J. MCNEILL, A. M. MONRO, J. PRADO, M. J. PRICE &amp; G. F. SMITH (2018). International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Veg. 159." title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="proceedings" year="2018">TURLAND et al., 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 14.1), a proposal to conserve Swartz’s name over Burman’s is in preparation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
